            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.58" />
                <note type="curatorial">House Collection</note>
                
                
                
                <note type="authorial">(copy of letter sent to Post)</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">58</fw>
                
                <opener>
                <address>
                <addrLine>Clark McAdams,</addrLine>
                
                <addrLine>P-D</addrLine>
                
                <addrLine>St. Louis</addrLine>
                </address>
                <salute>Dear Mr McAdams:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>In your letter <del>regarding</del> replying to my request for a leave of absence, you asked that I suggest a substitute. On the supposition, which may be wrong, that no one <del/> on the staff would be free to take over the work, <del>which requires</del> I would suggest Dr. Julius T. House of New River State College, West Va., who <del><unclear>edit</unclear></del> <add>for several years</add> has edited &amp; published "Present Day American Literature", one of the best of the independent magazines. Dr. House is a Chicago University man with a rich cultural background and with special training in Sociology. His <add>general</add> outlook is in perfect agreement with that which <del>your editorial page</del> makes your editorial page makes your editorial page a source of light.<del/></p>
                <closer>
                <salute>With kind thought</salute>
                
                <signed>Jno N</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">enc. letter dated June 25, '31</note>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
